# Command Surface Audit — WibWob-DOS

## TL;DR

- The C++ command registry is the real command source of truth (57 commands with descriptions), but the API/MCP layers currently lose or hide that metadata in multiple places.
- The biggest live failure is an IPC auth mismatch: C++ can require HMAC auth, but `tools/api_server/ipc_client.py` does not implement the handshake, so capability discovery can silently degrade to empty command lists.
- `/capabilities` intentionally strips command descriptions/params down to names only, and `/commands` still only exposes free-text hints (`description` + misnamed `requires_path`) instead of machine-readable parameter schemas.
- Python REST/FastAPI surfaces and the TUI menu both bypass the command registry extensively; many actions are duplicated with different behavior, and some registry commands are menu-only / API-only via `/menu/command`.
- Window type parity is broken: C++ supports more spawnable types than Python `WindowType`/`WindowCreate`, so `POST /windows` rejects valid C++ types (`quadra`, `snake`, `rogue`, `deep_signal`, `app_launcher`, `gallery`, `figlet_text`).

